FBIS3-15093 "drsov041_a_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-041 Document Type:Daily Report 2 Mar 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS More on Arrest of Suspected British Agent LD0103151194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1447 GMT 1 Mar 94 LD0103151194 Moscow ITAR-TASS Language: English Article Type:BFN ["Urgent" item by ITAR-TASS correspondent Andrey Palariya] [Text] Moscow March 1 TASS -- The Russian counterintelligence service arrested a leading Russian official from an organisation of the military-industrial complex who was spying for British secret services. The arrested is charged with treason in the form of espionage, TASS was told by the Federal Counterintelligence Service on Tuesday which added that the spy had been arrested on January 15 and faced criminal charges on January 25. The service said that, according to preliminary investigation, the official was equipped with special spying devices (cyphers, instructions on using hiding-places for supplying information to the British Embassy in Moscow). "On orders of British special services and for monetary remuneration the Russian citizen collected and passed classified information of military and economic character", the service said. The counterintelligence service said the spy had sold information on the latest Russian research in new armaments and their technical characteristics, on financing military research and development, on the state and prospects of Russian military cooperation with foreign countries.
